You can hurt someone with power tools by: 
1. Cutting them with a circular saw; 
2. Shrapnel from a nail gun; 
3. Shock or electric arc from a power tool; 
4. Injury from misuse or failure to exercise caution when operating power tools; 
5. Improperly used power tool causing objects to spin quickly; 
6. Charring from sparks or grit from grinding; 
7. Contact with hot parts or liquids.
